def: The glycerin salt of ricinoleic acid, occuring as acharacteristic constituent of castor oil; -- formerly called palmin.
Any animal that sucks blood; esp., the leech (Hirudomedicinalis), and related species.
A confectioner. [Obs.]He will take your daughters to be confectionaries, and to be cooks. 1Sam. viii. 13.
To collect again; to gather what has been scattered; as, to re-collect routed troops.God will one day raise the dead, re-collecting our scattered dust.Barrow.
Laborious. [Obs.] Wyatt.-- La"bor*ous*ly, adv. [Obs.] Sir T. Elyot.

To put a covering about; to wrap up or in; to inclose within acase, wrapper, integument or the like; to surround entirely; as, toenvelop goods or a letter; the fog envelops a ship.Nocturnal shades this world envelop. J. Philips.
A genus of coniferous trees, consisting of two species, SequoiaWashingtoniana, syn. S. gigantea, the "big tree" of California, andS. sempervirens, the redwood, both of which attain an immense height.
